      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "d4119849077f34a490bd916e3da6e9dc6dc88a35",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 19:07:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nWith ldiskfs's build system split from lustre in the previous patch, this patch goes to the next level and significantly reduces the unnecessary complexity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "f46a11c398f78fe331d707bd9dedec8f97ef82f5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 19:58:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nBuild Started http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/11057/ ",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "770a56b69aee5f74469e121d862317f70501808e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 20:17:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Verified\n\nBuild Successful \n \nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/11057/ : SUCCESS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "a70ae92d5546955fc409cde92bdf8cd75e318ed0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 20:43:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)\n\nWell, it builds at least.  :-)  I will wait to see what Maloo has to say before passing judgement any further.\n\nSomething that is sorely missing from the ldiskfs build is producing an ldiskfs-devel RPM which Lustre then uses to build against.\n\nDo you think that is valid work for this changeset, or ticket, at least or do you think that's a separate ticket altogether?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "ff88a05341887cbcb9cb20889a2e6909efdaec1b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 23:33:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)\n\nBrian, I completely agree with having ldiskfs-devel!\n\nWe've long thought that an ldiskfs-devel package was the way to go.  That way we can package headers or something that lustre can easily include, which allows lustre easily know which features are available rather than indirectly determining ldiskfs's features based on the kernel source or kernel version number.\n\nI think that is probably a requirement if we are going to really move ldiskfs out of the lustre tree, too.\n\nBut this commit is pretty large already, so lets leave that for a later patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "a9c66596f3a6789fc82891b7676718cc1b9f4839",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
